headlines.description: — Alec Burks scored a season-high 27 points off the bench, Killian Hayes added 25 and the Detroit Pistons spoiled LaMelo Ball’s return to the floor with a 141-134 overtime victory against the Charlotte Hornets on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Burks, Pistons spoil Ball's return to floor with OT win

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Indiana Pacers

headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton scored 29 points and the Indiana Pacers made 16 3-pointers to hold on for a 125-119 victory Wednesday night over the Golden State Warriors and Stephen Curry, who didn't finish the game because of a left shoulder injury.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry injures shoulder, Pacers hold off Warriors 125-119

headlines.description: — Franz Wagner scored 24 points, Orlando had a franchise-record 50 points in the first quarter and the Magic beat the Atlanta Hawks 135-124 on Wednesday night for their fourth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Magic beat Hawks 135-124 for 4th straight victory

headlines.description: — De’Aaron Fox had 27 points and 10 assists, Domantas Sabonis added 21 points and 20 rebounds and the Sacramento Kings held on to beat the Toronto Raptors 124-123 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fox has 27 points and 10 assists, Kings beat Raptors 124-123

events.name: New York Knicks at Chicago Bulls

headlines.description: — Julius Randle scored 31 points and Jalen Brunson added a season-high 30, including a 3-pointer with less than a minute left in overtime, and the New York Knicks won their fifth straight, 128-120 over the Chicago Bulls on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Randle, Brunson lead Knicks past Bulls 128-120 in OT

events.name: Miami Heat at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Tyler Herro made a career-high nine 3-pointers, hit the go-ahead jumper and scored 35 points in the Miami Heat’s 110-108 victory over the Oklahoma City Thunder on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Herro makes 9 3s, scores 35 points to lead Heat past Thunder

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — The Portland Trail Blazers are feeling better now that Damian Lillard is healthy.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lillard leads Blazers past Spurs 128-112 for 3rd straight

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell said he was thankful, in a strange way, for the playoff loss to Dallas last season because it helped send him to Cleveland.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell leads Cavs to 105-90 win over 2022 playoff foe Mavs

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had a season-high 43 points to go with 14 rebounds and eight assists, and the Denver Nuggets overcame strong games from former teammates Will Barton and Monte Morris to beat the undermanned Washington Wizards 141-128 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic scores 43 as Nuggets down ex-mates, Wizards 141-128
George has triple-double, Clippers beat Timberwolves 99-88
